  <Docs>
    <summary>Creates a theme specific look for drop shadow effects.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 The drop shadow effect creates a solid silhouette of the content of the element. This creates the illusion that the content is floating and casting a shadow.  
  
<a name="xamlObjectElementUsage_SDSC"></a>   
## XAML Object Element Usage  
  
```  
<theme:SystemDropShadowChrome ...>  
  singleChild  
</theme:SystemDropShadowChrome>  
```  
  
<a name="xamlValues_SDSC"></a>   
## XAML Values  
 `theme:`  
 An xmlns prefix for the <xref:Microsoft.Windows.Themes> CLR namespace. Typically, xmlns prefixes and mappings are defined in a XAML root element (not shown).  
  
 *singleChild*  
 A single object element child, representing the object that the decorator is drawn around. This object must be a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement>.  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
